שלוח: The Hebrew word שָׁלוּחַ (_shaluach_) has various meanings.
- It can mean “is sent” as in המכתב שלוח, (_hamichtav shaluach_, “the letter is sent.”)
- It can mean “something or someone who is sent” such as a messenger, (השלוח, _hashaluach_, the one who is sent.)
- The word שלוח comes from the [[shoresh שלח]]
- Grammatically, it is a [[passive participle]], specifically a [[pa’al passive participle]].
